race.comment: EXTREME DIAMOND (1) started in the red here first-up and proved too strong for the 66 graders over this trip. He's promising and judged on that he can take the next step for a top Sydney yard. BOOMTOWN CHAT (3) went close behind the above first-up and it was also a good effort after a slow start. Fitter and will be right in it again. FAMOSO (2) switched from a Victorian stable and first up impressed when beaten 1L this grade at Dubbo. Maps for the run of the race and has more up his sleeve. IOWNA BENZ (4) resumes for the Baker yard and showed plenty early doors. Her recent metro trials suggest she's back on track and she's won fresh. The tongue tie is applied for the first time.
